did.unittitle: Secretary of the Faculty for Arts, Sciences and Engineering Records

origination.label: Creator
origination.corpname: Graduate School of Arts and Sciences

physdesc.extent: Of the 433 digital objects, one contains 1,648 files.

did.abstract: The records consist of the minutes of faculty meetings in Tufts College, and later the schools of the Faculty of Arts and Sciences and the College of Engineering.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is organized in four series: Faculty meeting minutes; Subject and committee files; and Official papers, and Unprocessed accessions.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Index to the Faculty Meeting Minutes, 1981-88 in documentation folder. Numbering Note: File unit 001 contains 12 volumes that were previously housed on shelves in the DCA stacks (blue barcoded), making them items 1-12. Each volume was listed as both a file unit and an item in ReDiscovery. Due to their fragile state, these 12 volumes were housed together in a single record carton. As a result, the numbering of file units in this series skips from 1 to 13, but there are NO missing boxes or items between 2-12.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of the minutes of faculty meetings as well as supporting documentation. They record the actions taken by the faculty of Tufts College, and later the schools of the Faculty of Arts and Sciences (College of Liberal Arts, Jackson College, and the Graduate School of Arts and Sciences) and the College of Engineering. The records of the Fletcher School and the Medical, Dental and Veterinary, and Nutrition Schools are kept within each school's records.

processinfo.head: Processing status
processinfo.p: This collection is partially processed. Digital material from accession UA-2020-039 was processed by Records and Accessioning Archivist, Jane Kelly, in July 2020.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection contains some restricted material. Restrictions related to specific material are listed in the detailed contents list.This collection may require review before it is available for use. Please contact DCA for further details.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material in this collection may be protected by copyright and other rights. Please see "Reproductions and Use" on the Digital Collections and Archives website for more information about reproductions and permission to publish. Copyright to all materials created by Tufts University employees in the course of their work is held by the Trustees of Tufts University.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Secretary of the Faculty of Arts and Sciences was established in 1854, and has remained a position in the university's administration to the present day. The position's primary function has been to support faculty members in the school of Arts and Sciences through various means. This has entailed keeping minutes and agendas of regular faculty meetings. It has also necessitated the maintenance of subject files regarding various committees, curricula, and student life. Additionally, the Secretary of the Faculty facilitates communication between faculty of the Arts and Sciences, faculty of the School of Engineering, and the university administration. This responsibility has taken various forms, including keeping track of records from secretaries of the School of Engineering, and Tufts' graduate schools.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Secretary of the Faculty for Arts, Sciences and Engineering Records, 1854 -- 2019. Tufts University. Digital Collections and Archives. Medford, MA.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains meeting agendas, minutes, and related attachments of the Faculty of Arts and Sciences at Tufts College. Also contains records from the College of Engineering.
